  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Influenza is a major cause of morbidity and mortality. The investigators first goal is to
      evaluate soluble HLA-G5 isoform serum level as a potential marker of greater risk of death
      from Influenza respiratory illness in adult and pediatric patients hospitalized in
      reanimation. Secondly, the investigators collected respiratory samples in order to study the
      transcriptomic profiles of influenza-infected patients with severe symptoms.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
